Free for commercial use, no attribution required.  ST. LOUIS (Apr. 22, 2009) Chief Special Warfare Operator (SEAL) William Davis, assigned to the U.S. Navy Parachute Team, explains how he maneuvers his parachute to students at Ritenour High School during a St. Louis Navy Week event. St. Louis Navy Week is one of 21 Navy Weeks planned across America in 2009 and is designed to show Americans the investment they have made in their Navy and increase awareness in cities that do not have a significant Navy presence. (U.S. Navy photo by Mass Communication Specialist 2nd Class Michelle Kapica) File# 090422-N-5366K-040. Dated: 22.04.2009 - 22.04.2009.
